stage.name: Note1
stage.narrative:
Clean Up Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.
The cleanup action will be called automatically immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.

stage.name: Note2
stage.narrative:
Initialise Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.
The initialise action will be called automatically immediately after loading your business object.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.

stage.name: Handle Upcoming Popup
stage.narrative: You need to run this action in case if you expect some op window before the next action. It will launch a VBS script, which will look for the window named as the WindowTitle paramter. When it finds within the timout, then it will send some keys to that window. (eg. sending the hotkey button for a button,. etc.). This action is generally useful, due to that Blueprism will not stack on a process due to the popup window,

stage.name: VBS Script Popup
stage.narrative: Optional
stage.initialvalue:
'=== INFO ============================ 'Selecting a Window by Text and Sendking SendKeys
'=== USER INPUT ====================== WindowText = KeysToSend = ExpiryInSecondIfWindowNotfound = 1 DeleteThisScriptAfterRun = False StopFile = ""
'=== PROGRAM ========================= Set objFSO = CreateObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject") Set WshShell = WScript.CreateObject("WScript.Shell")
MaxTry = 0 Success = False
If (ExpiryInSecondIfWindowNotfound) = 0 Then ExpiryInSecondIfWindowNotfound = 1
Do WScript.Sleep 1000 If WshShell.AppActivate(WindowText) = True Then WshShell.AppActivate WindowText Success = True WshShell.Sendkeys KeysToSend End If
MaxTry = MaxTry + 1 Loop While Success = False And MaxTry <= ExpiryInSecondIfWindowNotfound
On Error Resume Next If DeleteThisScriptAfterRun Then objFSO.DeleteFile (WScript.ScriptFullName) On Error Goto 0
Set objFSO = Nothing Set WshShell = Nothing
